{"title_page": "Lucas Digne", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Lucas Digne\n| image = Save the Dream at the Match of Champions (31760339442) (cropped).jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = Digne lining up for [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in 2016\n| fullname = Lucas Digne<ref>{{cite web |url=http://actas.rfef.es/actas/RFEF_CmpActa1?cod_primaria=1000144&CodActa=43261 |title=Acta del Partido celebrado el 26 de agosto de 2017, en Vitoria-Gasteiz |trans-title=Minutes of the Match held on 26 August 2017, in Vitoria-Gasteiz |publisher=Royal Spanish Football Federation |accessdate=13 June 2019 |language=Spanish}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1993|7|20|df=y}}<ref name=PremProfile>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/players/5758/Lucas-Digne/overview |title=Lucas Digne: Overview |publisher=Premier League |accessdate=13 June 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Meaux]], France\n| height = 1.78 m<ref name=PremProfile/>\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Left-back]]\n| currentclub = [[Everton F.C.|Everton]]\n| clubnumber = 12\n| youthyears1 = 1999\u20132002\n| youthclubs1 = Mareuil-sur-Ourcq\n| youthyears2 = 2002\u20132005\n| youthclubs2 = Cr\u00e9py-en-Valois\n| youthyears3 = 2005\u20132010\n| youthclubs3 = [[Lille OSC|Lille]]\n| years1 = 2010\u20132011\n| clubs1 = [[Lille OSC|Lille B]]\n| caps1 = 36\n| goals1 = 1\n| years2 = 2011\u20132013\n| clubs2 = [[Lille OSC|Lille]]\n| caps2 = 49\n| goals2 = 2\n| years3 = 2013\u20132016\n| clubs3 = [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]]\n| caps3 = 29\n| goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2015\u20132016\n| clubs4 = \u2192 [[A.S. Roma|Roma]] (loan)\n| caps4 = 33\n| goals4 = 3\n| years5 = 2016\u20132018\n| clubs5 = [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]]\n| caps5 = 29\n| goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2018\u2013\n| clubs6 = [[Everton F.C.|Everton]]\n| caps6 = 59\n| goals6 = 4\n| nationalyears1 = 2008\u20132009\n| nationalteam1 = [[France national under-16 football team|France U16]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 15\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2009\u20132010\n| nationalteam2 = [[France national under-17 football team|France U17]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 15\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2010\u20132011\n| nationalteam3 = [[France national under-18 football team|France U18]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 11\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| nationalyears4 = 2011\u20132012\n| nationalteam4 = [[France national under-19 football team|France U19]]\n| nationalcaps4 = 12\n| nationalgoals4 = 1\n| nationalyears5 = 2013\n| nationalteam5 = [[France national under-20 football team|France U20]]\n| nationalcaps5 = 12\n| nationalgoals5 = 2\n| nationalyears6 = 2013\n| nationalteam6 = [[France national under-21 football team|France U21]]\n| nationalcaps6 = 7\n| nationalgoals6 = 0\n| nationalyears7 = 2014\u2013\n| nationalteam7 = [[France national football team|France]]\n| nationalcaps7 = 30\n| nationalgoals7 = 0\n| club-update = 1 February 2020\n| nationalteam-update = 18 November 2019\n| medaltemplates = {{Medal|Sport|Men's [[Association football|football]]}}\n{{Medal|Country|{{fb|FRA}}}}\n{{Medal|Comp|[[UEFA European Championship]]}}\n{{Medal|RU|[[UEFA Euro 2016|2016 France]]|}}\n}}\n'''Lucas Digne''' ({{IPA-fr|lyk\u0251 di\u0272}}; born 20 July 1993) is a French professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|left-back]] for {{English football updater|Everton}} club [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] and the [[France national football team|France national team]].\n\nDigne began his career at [[Lille OSC|Lille]] before joining [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] in 2013. After spending a season on loan at [[A.S. Roma|Roma]], he moved to [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in July 2016. Despite not playing regularly at either club, he won 12 honours at Paris and Barcelona combined. He joined Everton in August 2018.\n\nHe won the [[2013 FIFA U-20 World Cup|2013 World Cup]] with [[France national under-20 football team|France under-20]], and made his senior international debut in March 2014. He represented [[France national football team|France]] at the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]] and [[UEFA Euro 2016]], where his nation reached the final.\n\n== Club career ==\n=== Lille ===\n[[File:Lucas Digne (LOSC).JPG|thumb|left|upright|Digne playing for [[Lille OSC|Lille]] in 2012]]\nBorn in [[Meaux]], [[Seine-et-Marne]], Digne finished his development at [[Lille OSC|Lille]], signing his first professional contract on 27 July 2010 for three years.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.losc.fr/filInfo.php?id=2835 |title=Digne et le LOSC li\u00e9s jusqu'en 2013 |date=27 July 2010 |work=[[Lille OSC]] |accessdate=2 August 2010 |language=French}}{{dead link|date=May 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Ahead of the [[2011\u201312 Ligue 1|2011\u201312 season]], Digne was promoted to the senior team permanently and assigned the number 3 shirt. He made his professional debut on 26 October 2011 in a 6\u20131 victory over [[CS Sedan Ardennes|Sedan]] in the last 16 of the [[Coupe de la Ligue]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.lfp.fr/coupeLigue/feuille_match/75645 |title=Lille v. Sedan Match Report |date=6 October 2011 |work=[[Ligue de Football Professionnel]] |accessdate=26 October 2011 |language=French}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2012, Digne extended his contract until 2016.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lucas Digne prolonge \u00e0 Lille |trans-title=Lucas Digne prolongs at Lille |url=http://sport24.lefigaro.fr/football/ligue-1/Homes-Clubs/lille/fil-info/lucas-digne-prolonge-a-lille-527131 |accessdate=31 July 2018 |work=Le Figaro |date=10 January 2012 |language=French}}</ref> On 28 January, he made his [[Ligue 1]] debut at the [[Stadium Nord Lille Metropole]], playing the final two minutes of a 3\u20130 win over [[AS Saint-\u00c9tienne|Saint-\u00c9tienne]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Les Dogues passent au vert ! |trans-title=The ''Dogues'' go at the green! |url=https://www.losc.fr/actualites-foot-lille/losc-asse-3-0-les-dogues-passent-au-vert |accessdate=31 July 2018 |publisher=Lille OSC |date=28 January 2012 |language=Spanish}}</ref> He totalled 16 league appearances as the defending champions came third.\n\nDigne was a regular in the 2012\u201313 season. On 23 February 2013, having given Lille the lead in a 3\u20131 win at [[AC Ajaccio|Ajaccio]] when his cross was deflected in by [[Yoann Poulard]], he was sent off after an hour for a foul on [[Matthieu Chalm\u00e9]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Ten-man Lille ease to victory |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/ac-ajaccio-vs-lille/259888 |accessdate=1 August 2018 |publisher=Sky Sports |date=23 February 2013}}</ref> He scored his first goal on 7 April, a penalty in a 5\u20130 home win over [[FC Lorient|Lorient]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Kalou at the double for Lille |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/lille-vs-lorient/284955 |accessdate=1 August 2018 |publisher=Sky Sports |date=7 April 2013}}</ref> and two weeks later he added another to equalise in a 2\u20131 comeback victory at [[SC Bastia|Bastia]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Lille fight back at Bastia |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/bastia-vs-lille/260036 |accessdate=1 August 2018 |publisher=Sky Sports |date=21 April 2013}}</ref>\n\n=== Paris Saint-Germain ===\nOn 17 July 2013, Digne signed a five-year deal with [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]],<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.psg.fr/en/News/003001/Article/62873/Lucas-Digne-signs-five-year-deal-with-Paris-Saint-Germain |title=LUCAS DIGNE SIGNS FIVE-YEAR DEAL WITH PARIS SAINT-GERMAIN |date=17 July 2013 |accessdate=17 July 2013 |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain F.C.}}</ref> on a fee believed to be around \u20ac15&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.goal.com/en-us/news/69/transfer-zone/2013/07/17/4124637/paris-saint-germain-seals-digne-deal |title=Paris Saint-Germain seals Digne deal |date=17 July 2013 |accessdate=17 July 2013 |publisher=Goal.com}}</ref> On 3 August, he was an unused substitute as they won the [[2013 Troph\u00e9e des Champions]] with a 2\u20131 victory over [[FC Girondins de Bordeaux|Bordeaux]] in Gabon.<ref>{{cite news |title=Paris Saint-Germain 2\u20131 Girondins de Bordeaux |url=https://www.lfp.fr/tropheeChampions/feuille_match/78274 |accessdate=31 July 2018 |publisher=LFP |date=3 August 2013}}</ref> He did not make his debut until 13 September in a 2\u20130 win at the same opponents, as manager [[Laurent Blanc]] rotated his squad ahead of the [[UEFA Champions League]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Digne to get his chance in Bordeaux? |url=https://www.ligue1.com/ligue1/article/digne-to-get-his-chance-in-bordeaux.htm |accessdate=31 July 2018 |publisher=Ligue 1 |date=10 September 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Digne et Ongenda titulaires avec le PSG \u00e0 Bordeaux|trans-title=Digne and Ongenda starters for PSG at Bordeaux |url=http://www.leparisien.fr/flash-actualite-sports/ligue-1-digne-et-ongenda-titulaires-avec-le-psg-a-bordeaux-13-09-2013-3134467.php |accessdate=31 July 2018 |work=Le Parisien |date=13 September 2013 |language=French}}</ref> PSG ended the season with both the league and league cup titles, though Digne was back-up to Brazilian veteran [[Maxwell (footballer, born 1981)|Maxwell]].<ref name=four/>\n\nDigne played the full 90 minutes in the [[2014 Troph\u00e9e des Champions]], which PSG won 2\u20130 against [[EA Guingamp|Guingamp]] in Beijing.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Maltret |first1=Laurent |title=Paris brille \u00e0 P\u00e9kin |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/match/316940 |accessdate=31 July 2018 |work=L'\u00c9quipe |date=2 August 2014 |language=French}}</ref> The Parisians won all four domestic honours in 2014\u201315, with Digne an unused substitute in their Coupe de France and Coupe de la Ligue final victories.\n\n==== Roma (loan) ====\nOn 26 August 2015, Italian [[Serie A]] club [[A.S. Roma|Roma]] signed Digne from PSG on a season-long loan deal for \u20ac2.5&nbsp;million, with the option to make the move permanent at the end of the [[2015\u201316 A.S. Roma season|season]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.asroma.it/en/news/roma_complete_signing_of_lucas_digne |title=Roma complete signing of Lucas Digne |date=26 August 2015 |publisher=[[A.S. Roma]] |accessdate=26 August 2015}}</ref> He made his debut five days later, playing the entire match in a 2\u20131 victory against title holders [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]] at the [[Stadio Olimpico]]. He blew a sarcastic kiss at opponent [[Roberto Pereyra]] and advised him to check the scoreboard, a gesture likened to one by Roma captain [[Francesco Totti]] to [[Igor Tudor]] of the same rival in a 4\u20130 win in February 2004.<ref>{{cite news |title=Roma, Digne come Totti: sfott\u00f2 alla Juve per il risultato |trans-title=Roma, Digne like Totti: teased Juventus for the result |url=https://sport.sky.it/calcio/2015/08/31/digne-come-totti-sfotto-risultato-roma-juve.html |accessdate=2 August 2018 |publisher=Sky Sports |date=31 August 2015 |language=Italian}}</ref>\n\nDigne scored his first goal for the ''Giallorossi'' on 26 September with a close-range header in a 5\u20131 home win over [[Carpi F.C. 1909|Carpi]], having earlier assisted [[Kostas Manolas]] in opening his account for the club.<ref>{{cite news |title=Roma 5 Carpi 1: Garcia's five-star men leave new boys winless |url=http://www.beinsports.com/en/football/news/roma-5-carpi-1-garcias-five-star-men-leave-1/103943 |accessdate=2 August 2018 |publisher=beIN Sports |date=26 September 2015}}</ref> Against the same opponents on 12 February, he returned from injury to score from 30 metres in a 3\u20131 win,<ref>{{cite news |title=Le superbe but de Lucas Digne (AS Roma) face \u00e0 Carpi|trans-title=Lucas Digne's (AS Roma) superb goal against Carpi |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Le-superbe-but-de-lucas-digne-as-roma-face-a-carpi/634098 |accessdate=2 August 2018 |work=L'\u00c9quipe |date=12 February 2016 |language=French}}</ref> and on 17 April he opened a 3\u20133 draw at [[Atalanta B.C.|Atalanta]].<ref>{{cite news |title=10 facts and figures on Atalanta 3\u20133 Roma |url=http://www.asroma.com/en/news/2016/4/10-facts-and-figures-on-atalanta-3-3-roma |accessdate=2 August 2018 |publisher=AS Roma |date=19 April 2016}}</ref> The team from Italy's [[Rome|capital]] came third in Serie A, and Digne declared that he wanted the move to be made permanent.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Rodden |first1=Mark |title=Paris Saint-Germain defender Lucas Digne wants permanent Roma move |url=http://www.espn.co.uk/football/soccer-transfers/story/2874642/paris-saint-germain-defender-lucas-digne-wants-permanent-roma-move |accessdate=2 August 2018 |publisher=ESPN FC |date=17 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n=== Barcelona ===\nOn 13 July 2016, Digne joined Spanish [[La Liga]] side [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] on a five-year deal. The fee was \u20ac16.5&nbsp;million (\u00a313.8&nbsp;million), with the possibility to increase to \u20ac20.5&nbsp;million (\u00a317.1&nbsp;million), according to individual and team results.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/football/first-team/news/2016-2017/lucas-digne-becomes-fc-barcelona-s-latest-signing |title=Lucas Digne becomes FC Barcelona's latest signing |publisher=FC Barcelona |date=13 July 2016 |accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref> On 14 August 2016, Digne made his first appearance for Barcelona in a 0\u20132 victory against [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] in the [[2016 Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a]] first leg, as a 27th-minute substitute for compatriot [[J\u00e9r\u00e9my Mathieu]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.barcablaugranes.com/2016/8/15/12479424/barcelonas-lucas-digne-impresses-on-debut-vs-sevilla |title=Barcelona's Lucas Digne Impresses on Debut vs. Sevilla |last=Mazariegos |first=Luis |date=2016-08-15 |website=Barca Blaugranes|access-date=2016-08-16}}</ref>\n\nHe played 26 total games in his first season at the [[Camp Nou]], scoring once in a 7\u20130 (8\u20131 aggregate) win over [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B]] club [[H\u00e9rcules CF|H\u00e9rcules]] in the last 32 of the [[Copa del Rey]] on 21 December 2016.<ref>{{cite news |title=Barcelona 7\u20130 H\u00e9rcules |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38339837 |accessdate=29 July 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=21 December 2016}}</ref> Barcelona won that cup, with Digne unused in the [[2017 Copa del Rey Final|final]] on 27 May 2017, a 3\u20131 win over [[Deportivo Alav\u00e9s|Alav\u00e9s]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Barcelona 3\u20131 Alaves |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39909498 |accessdate=1 August 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=27 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nDigne played 20 times in [[2017\u201318 FC Barcelona season|2017\u201318]] as Barcelona won the league and cup [[Double (association football)|double]] under new manager [[Ernesto Valverde]]. On 18 October 2017, he scored from [[Lionel Messi]]'s assist in a 3\u20131 home win over [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]] in the Champions League group stage.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Unwin |first1=Will |title=Barcelona 3\u20131 Olympiakos: Lionel Messi scores 100th European goal as Gerard Pique sees red |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/barcelona-vs-olympiakos/384284 |accessdate=29 July 2018 |publisher=Sky Sports |date=19 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Everton ===\n[[File:Lucas Digne Everton.jpg|thumb|180px|left|Lucas Digne playing for [[Everton Football Club|Everton]] in a friendly game against [[FC Sion]].]]\nDigne joined English club [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] on 1 August 2018, for a five-year deal on an initial fee of \u00a318 million.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lucas Digne: Everton sign full-back from Barcelona for \u00a318m |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45024174 |accessdate=1 August 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=1 August 2018}}</ref> He made his debut ten days later, replacing double goalscorer and fellow debutant [[Richarlison]] for the last four minutes of a 2\u20132 draw at [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hafez |first1=Shamoon |title=Wolverhampton Wanderers 2\u20132 Everton |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45067374 |accessdate=11 August 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=11 August 2018}}</ref> On his first start on 29 August in a 3\u20131 [[EFL Cup]] win against [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]], he assisted a goal from [[Dominic Calvert-Lewin]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Lucas Digne shines on full debut for Everton |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45266834 |accessdate=29 August 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=29 August 2018}}</ref> Digne made his first [[Premier League]] start for Everton four days later in a home game against [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]], and assisted Dominic Calvert-Lewin's headed equaliser in a 1\u20131 draw.<ref>{{cite news |title=Everton maintain their unbeaten start |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45305226 |accessdate=1 September 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=1 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nBy the start of October, Digne had become Everton's first-choice left back, ahead of veteran [[Leighton Baines]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jones |first1=Adam |title=How Lucas Digne has firmly cemented his place in Everton's first team ahead of Leighton Baines |url=https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/how-lucas-digne-firmly-cemented-15241440 |accessdate=24 January 2019 |work=Liverpool Echo |date=5 October 2018}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club on 10 December, in the sixth minute of stoppage time at the end of a match against [[Watford F.C.|Watford]], curling in a free kick for a 2\u20132 draw.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lucas Digne first Everton goal |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46422266 |accessdate=10 December 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=10 December 2018}}</ref> Sixteen days later he scored twice in a 5\u20131 win at [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]], with a free kick and a 30-yard shot.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lucas Digne at the double |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46615195 |accessdate=26 December 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=26 December 2018}}</ref> On 29 January 2019 he was sent off in a 1\u20130 win at Huddersfield for denying [[Adama Diakhaby]] a goalscoring opportunity with a foul.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Begley |first1=Emlyn |title=Huddersfield Town 0&ndash;1 Everton |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46955252 |accessdate=29 January 2019 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=29 January 2019}}</ref> Digne's first season at Everton concluded with individual honours as he was named the Club\u2019s Player of the Season, as voted for by supporters, and Players\u2019 Player of the Season alongside midfielder [[Idrissa Gueye|Idrissa Gana Gueye]], the first time the award had been shared. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.evertonfc.com/news/2019/05/14/dixies|title=Digne Honoured After Scooping Dixies Double {{!}} Everton Football Club|website=www.evertonfc.com|access-date=2019-05-15}}</ref> He didn't preforme well enough to stay a Spanish giants (Barcelona) so he left to go Everton.\n\n== International career ==\n[[File:Lucas DIGNE.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Digne with the [[France national under-19 football team|France U19s]] in 2012]]\n\nDigne was a [[France national youth football team|French youth international]] and represented his nation at the [[France national under-16 football team|U16]], [[France national under-17 football team|U17]], and [[France national under-18 football team|U18]] levels. At the [[2013 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in Turkey, he played every match as [[France national under-20 football team|France]] won the title.<ref name=four>{{cite news |last1=Sehdev |first1=Aman |title=Meet the French left-back set to make Patrice Evra sweat for his World Cup place |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/meet-french-left-back-set-make-patrice-evra-sweat-his-world-cup-place |accessdate=31 July 2018 |work=FourFourTwo |date=28 May 2014}}</ref>\n\nHe was first called up for the [[France national football team|senior side]] in February 2014, ahead of a friendly match against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] on 5 March.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Absalon |first1=Julien |title=\u00c9quipe de France : Digne et Griezmann retenus pour affronter les Pays-Bas |trans-title=France team: Digne and Griezmann retained to face the Netherlands |url=https://www.rtl.fr/sport/equipe-de-france-griezmann-et-digne-retenus-pour-affronter-les-pays-bas-7770054824 |accessdate=31 July 2018 |publisher=RTL |date=27 February 2014 |language=French}}</ref> He debuted in that match, as a half-time substitute for [[Patrice Evra]] in a 2\u20130 win at the [[Stade de France]].<ref>{{cite news |title=International friendly: France ease to a 2\u20130 win over Holland in Paris |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/france-vs-netherlands/305330 |accessdate=31 July 2018 |publisher=Sky Sports |date=6 March 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn June, manager [[Didier Deschamps]] named Digne as one of 23 members of the French squad for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]] in Brazil, wearing the number 17 shirt.<ref>{{cite news |title=France squad for 2014 World Cup: the 23 chosen by Didier Deschamps |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2014/jun/05/france-squad-2014-world-cup |accessdate=31 July 2018 |work=The Guardian |date=5 June 2014}}</ref> His one appearance for the eventual quarter-finalists was the third group game against [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]], in which he suffered a foul that earned the Ecuadorian captain [[Antonio Valencia]] a straight red card.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Cruise |first1=Ian |title=Ecuador 0\u20130 France: Antonio Valencia sees red as South Americans bow out |url=https://talksport.com/football/167607/ecuador-0-0-france-antonio-valencia-sees-red-south-americans-bow-out-14062598379/ |accessdate=31 July 2018 |publisher=Talksport |date=25 June 2014}}</ref>\n\nDigne was chosen for the French squad that came runners-up on home soil at [[UEFA Euro 2016]], but did not play.<ref>{{cite news |title=Euro 2016: Leicester's N'Golo Kante in France squad |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36282689 |accessdate=31 July 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=12 May 2016}}</ref> He was put on standby for the squad at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Benson |first1=Michael |title=World Cup 2018: Chelsea, Manchester United and Manchester City stars included in France's squad for finals |url=https://talksport.com/football/world-cup-2018-chelsea-manchester-united-and-manchester-city-stars-included-frances-squad |accessdate=24 May 2018 |publisher=Talksport |date=17 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nDigne was in [[Barcelona]] when it was [[2017 Barcelona attacks|hit by a terror attack]] on 17 August 2017, and gave first aid to the victims.<ref>{{cite news |title=Barcelona's Lucas Digne aided wounded after deadly attack \u2013 sources |url=http://www.espn.co.uk/football/barcelona/story/3185507/barcelonas-lucas-digne-aided-wounded-after-deadly-attack-sources |accessdate=29 July 2018 |publisher=ESPN FC |date=21 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Digne gave first aid to Barcelona attack victims |url=http://www.marca.com/en/football/barcelona/2017/08/21/599b14c746163fb0098b461b.html |accessdate=29 July 2018 |work=Marca |date=21 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Bartlett |first1=Evan |title=Barcelona defender Lucas Digne 'helped terror attack victims with water bottles and homemade tourniquets' |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/european/barcelona-defender-lucas-dignes-terror-attack-victims-water-bottles-homemade-tourniquets-football-a7906571.html |accessdate=29 July 2018 |work=The Independent |date=22 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Career statistics ==\n=== Club ===\n{{updated|match played 1 February 2020}}<ref name=\"Soccerway\">{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/lucas-digne/138198/ |title=L. Digne: Summary |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |accessdate=12 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|National Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Europe\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Lille OSC|Lille]]\n|[[2011\u201312 Ligue 1|2011\u201312]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Ligue 1]]\n|16||0||1||0||1||0||colspan=4|\u2014||18||0\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Ligue 1|2012\u201313]]\n|33||2||2||0||1||0||5<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"UCL\">All appearances in [[UEFA Champions League]]</ref>||0||colspan=2|\u2014||41||2\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!49!!2!!3!!0!!2!!0!!5!!0!!colspan=2|\u2014!!59!!2\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]]\n|[[2013\u201314 Ligue 1|2013\u201314]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Ligue 1\n|15||0||1||0||2||0||2<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"UCL\"/>||0||colspan=2|\u2014||20||0\n|-\n|[[2014\u201315 Ligue 1|2014\u201315]]\n|14||0||5||0||2||0||1<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"UCL\"/>||0||1<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"TDC\">All appearances in [[Troph\u00e9e des Champions]]</ref>||0||23||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!29!!0!!6!!0!!4!!0!!3!!0!!1!!0!!43!!0\n|-\n|[[A.S. Roma|Roma]] (loan)\n|[[2015\u201316 Serie A|2015\u201316]]\n|[[Serie A]]\n|33||3||1||0||colspan=2|\u2014||8<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"UCL\"/>||0||0||0||42||3\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]]\n|[[2016\u201317 FC Barcelona season|2016\u201317]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[La Liga]]\n|17||0||3||1||colspan=2|\u2014||4<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"UCL\"/>||0||2<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"SDE\">All appearances in [[Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a]]</ref>||0||26||1\n|-\n|[[2017\u201318 FC Barcelona season|2017\u201318]]\n|12||0||4||0||colspan=2|\u2014||3<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"UCL\"/>||1||1<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"SDE\"/>||0||20||1\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!29!!0!!7!!1!!colspan=2|\u2014!!7!!1!!3!!0!!46!!2\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Everton F.C.|Everton]]\n|[[2018\u201319 Everton F.C. season|2018\u201319]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Premier League]]\n|35||4||1||0||1||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||37||4\n|-\n|[[2019\u201320 Everton F.C. season|2019\u201320]]\n|24||0||0||0||3||1||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||27||1\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!59!!4!!1!!0!!4!!1!!colspan=2|\u2014!!colspan=2|\u2014!!64!!5\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!199!!9!!18!!1!!10!!1!!23!!1!!4!!0!!253!!12\n|}\n\n{{Reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n=== International ===\n<!-- NOTE: when updating stats, update the infobox too! -->\n{{updated|match played 18 November 2019}}<ref>{{NFT player|id=54749|name=Digne, Lucas |accessdate=26 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by national team and year\n|-\n! National team!!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\"|[[France national football team|France]]\n|2014||8||0\n|-\n|2015||2||0\n|-\n|2016||5||0\n|-\n|2017||5||0\n|-\n|2018||3||0\n|-\n|2019||7||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total!!30!!0\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Paris Saint-Germain'''\n*[[Ligue 1]]: [[2013\u201314 Ligue 1|2013\u201314]], [[2014\u201315 Ligue 1|2014\u201315]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/>\n*[[Coupe de France]]: [[2014\u201315 Coupe de France|2014\u201315]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/>\n*[[Coupe de la Ligue]]: [[2013\u201314 Coupe de la Ligue|2013\u201314]], [[2014\u201315 Coupe de la Ligue|2014\u201315]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/>\n*[[Troph\u00e9e des Champions]]: [[2013 Troph\u00e9e des Champions|2013]], [[2014 Troph\u00e9e des Champions|2014]], [[2015 Troph\u00e9e des Champions|2015]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/>\n\n'''Barcelona'''\n*[[La Liga]]: [[2017\u201318 La Liga|2017\u201318]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/>\n*[[Copa del Rey]]: [[2016\u201317 Copa del Rey|2016\u201317]], [[2017\u201318 Copa del Rey|2017\u201318]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/>\n*[[Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a]]: [[2016 Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a|2016]]<ref nam